F underscore send transaction is used if your solidity function has neither view pure or constant. When you use ethical, it means that your function will not modify the Ethereum blockchain and you will not spend any ether for the execution of the function. When you use eth underscore send transaction, it means that your function will potentially modify the Ethereum blockchain and that the execution of the function will cost ether.
